:28:10Z"},{"id":"6194","title":"The right to bathe","slug":"bathing-should-be-a-right-in-21st-century-cities","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"Bathing should be a right in 21st-century cities","standfirstLong":"Water is a great healer. Can New York’s public pools and ‘blue spaces’ be engineered for collective hydrotherapy?","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":"white","cardPlayIconColor":"white","alignX":"center","alignY":"top","backdropStrength":1},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"187129","name":"Rebecca Hayes Jacobs"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/94896f0b-913e-4d2c-b272-cc7b8a534dd7/essay-final-240125_06_psyche_v005.jpg","alt":"A colour illustration of a pool of water in which many people are swimming, glimpsed through trees, against a city skyline background","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Mental health","slug":"mental-health"},"topics":[{"slug":"mental-health","title":"Mental health"},{"slug":"nature-and-landscape","title":"Nature and landscape"},{"slug":"public-health","title":"Public health"}],"section":{"title":"Psychology","slug":"psychology"},"createdAt":"2024-01-15T11:23:56Z"},{"id":"6186","title":"On knowing who he was","slug":"how-alan-watts-re-imagined-religion-desire-and-life-itself","type":"essay","audio":null,"standfirstShort":"How Alan Watts re-imagined religion, desire and life itself","standfirstLong":"Alan Watts, for all his faults, was a wildly imaginative and provocative thinker who reimagined religion in a secular age","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":"white","cardPlayIconColor":"white","alignX":"left","alignY":"bottom","backdropStrength":2},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"49","name":"Christopher Harding"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/f083b74a-b459-44d2-8278-87da0ecfd6b7/essay-watts-final-cwab8r.jpg","alt":"","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Thinkers and theor